articles.description: Demajeo Wiggins had 17 points and 15 rebounds -- his 10th double-double of the season -- and Matt Fox scored 12 points, including a critical 3-pointer, and Bowling Green beat Eastern Michigan 70-63 in overtime on Saturday.
articles.headline: Wiggins, Fox help Bowling Green beat E. Michigan in OT

articles.description: Nick McGlynn scored 17 points and Drake led virtually the entire way in taking a 71-64 victory over Northern Iowa on Saturday.
articles.headline: McGlynn scores 17, Drake beats Northern Iowa 71-64

articles.description: Otis Livingston II scored 14 points, Jaire Grayer added 12 points and 12 rebounds and George Mason held off George Washington for a 72-65 victory on Saturday.
articles.headline: George Mason holds off George Washington, wins 72-65

articles.description: Taylor Funk scored 22 points and Saint Joseph's closed fast to post an 85-73 win over Massachusetts in an Atlantic 10 showdown Saturday afternoon.
articles.headline: Funk scores 22, leads Saint Joseph's past UMass, 85-73

articles.description: Sixth-ranked Cincinnati owns a 15-game winning streak and a three-game lead in the American Athletic Conference standings as it rolls into Dallas to play Southern Methodist on Sunday at Moody Coliseum.
articles.headline: No. 6 Cincinnati wary of SMU's home presence

articles.description: Sean Hoehn scored 22 points, De'Von Barnett scored 16 and Sacred Heart defeated Central Connecticut 67-50 on Saturday.
articles.headline: Hoehn, Sacred Heart beats Central Connecticut State 67-50

videos.description: Davion Mitchell waits for Anfernee McLemore's pick, then Mitchell threads a pass to him for the two-handed slam.
videos.headline: Mitchell makes sweet dish leads to dunk for Auburn

videos.description: As the shot clock is winding down, Bryce Brown double-clutches to knock down a  3-pointer.
videos.headline: Auburn's Brown makes crazy 3-pointer

videos.description: Mustapha Heron drives baseline and throws down a vicious jam on Derek Ogbeide.
videos.headline: Tigers' Heron puts defender on a poster

videos.description: Jared Harper gets the rebound and takes off to finish the double-clutch layup.
videos.headline: Tigers' Harper takes it coast-to-coast

videos.description: Bryce Brown pulls up from deep and knocks down a 3-pointer and head coach Bruce Pearl rewards him with a high-five.
videos.headline: Brown gets Pearl's approval after bucket

videos.description: Bryce Brown finishes through contact bucket, then celebrates the foul call by flexing his muscles.
videos.headline: Auburn's Brown flexes after tough bucket

videos.description: Bryce Brown intercepts a pass, drives, finishes through contact with his left hand and celebrates by flexing his muscles again.
videos.headline: Brown flexing on the bulldogs

videos.description: Bryce Brown scores a game-high 28 points as the No. 17 Tigers top the Bulldogs 79-65.
videos.headline: Auburn rolls against Georgia

videos.description: The Tigers trail by 14 points at the half, but come out and beat the Bulldogs 79-65.
videos.headline: Second-half surge leads No. 17 Auburn to win vs. UGA
